The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | 1-WICKET WIN IN TESTS
                                                                                                                       7                                      1-WICKET WIN IN TESTS
                            
	Indias one-wicket win over Australia in Mohali, on Tuesday, was the 12th instance of a team winning by such a margin. The following is the list:         
	 England bt Australia, The Oval, 1902         
	 South Africa bt England, Johannesburg, 1905-06         
	 England bt Australia, Melbourne, 1907-08         
	 England bt South Africa, Cape Town, 1922-23         
	 Australia bt West Indies, Melbourne, 1951-52         
	 New Zealand bt West Indies, Dunedin, 1979-80         
	 Pakistan bt Australia, Karachi, 1994-95         
	 West Indies bt Australia, Bridgetown, 1998-99         
	 West Indies bt Pakistan, St Johns, 1999-2000         
	 Pakistan bt Bangladesh, Multan, 2003-04         
	 Sri Lanka bt South Africa, Colombo PSS, 2006         
	 India bt Australia, Mohali, 2010-11         
	Note: This was Indias first one-wicket win in Tests and Australias 5th such loss         
	Mohandas Menon                                                                                                                       
